      About this item

      • CONTROL FROM ANYWHERE: With the nest, you're able to make changes to the current temperature, wherever this unit is attached, with your laptop, phone or tablet. In addition to this, you are able to utilize voice commands by home assistant, allowing you to command this unit hands-free.
      • EASY TO INSTALL: This unit is designed to install where needed in 60 minutes or less. This smart thermostat quickly and easily replaces your previous unit. You have two options for installation: place it on the optional stand (sold separately) or install it on the wall in place of your old thermostat.
      • SCHEDULE YOUR TEMPERATURE: With the app, you are easily able to set a scheduled time for temperature adjustment in the household. Whether you tune it for maximum comfort or variable temperatures to help with energy usage, you'll always have complete control. The choice and customizability is yours to maintain for your own household.
      • WIDE RANGE COMPATIBILITY: The Nest Thermostat E works with most of 24V heating and cooling systems, including gas, electric, forced air, heat pump, radiant, oil, hot water, solar and geothermal. This unit is designed to work even if your home has a C-wire, but you may have to install a new one. If you're unsure of how to setup a C-wire, we recommend reaching out to a Nest pro in your area.
      • SUBTLE AND SIMPLE: The Nest E is designed to blend in with its surroundings and not interrupt the creative design of your household, especially with lightly colored walls. The unit also features manual controls via the front of the device, with a simplistic spin dial. Create and embrace ease and comfort with the Google Nest.

          Product Description

          The Product
          The Nest E Pro from Google is an affordable smart thermostat that learns your heating and cooling preferences to optimize your comfort needs. This adds up to substantial savings on your monthly energy bill. Control it from any location with the Nest app on your smartphone, tablet or PC.

          Energy Savings
          Nest is the first thermostat to be ENERGY STAR certified by the EPA. Customers saved an average of 10% to 12% on heating bills and 15% on cooling bills, according to several years of study. Check your energy history within the Nest app to see how much you're saving and ways to save more. The Nest Leaf appears on the display when the temperature is set at an energy-saving level.

          Smart Features
          The Nest thermostat controls temperature automatically by learning your habits, then programming itself to suit your lifestyle. Use it like you would a regular thermostat for a week by adjusting the temperature as normal. After several days, Nest will program itself to keep your home comfortable based on your schedule. It automatically turns down when you're away from the house by using your phone's location. Additionally, you can lock your thermostat to prevent adjustment unless the user can enter a short, chosen code.

          Updated Design
          The Nest E Pro features a subtler design and a lightweight polycarbonate build. The frosted display blends in with light colored walls and wall coverings. It is easily controlled with a spin dial that wraps around the device.

          How customer reviews and ratings work

          Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

          To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

          • Teju
            5.0 out of 5 stars Works great with 2-wire heat only Top-Vent Gravity Wall Furnace
            Reviewed in the United States on December 1, 2024
            Verified Purchase
            If you have a 2-wire system that's heat or cool only, this thermostat will work for you. It will work a system is a millivolt or 24V system.

            For a millivolt furnace like the Williams Top-Vent Gravity Wall Furnace, you'll need a 24V transformer to act a C wire to provide power to the thermostat. You can search for transformers that work with Nest on Amazon. One such example is the Viivria AC 24 Volt Transformer. Once you have your transformer,

            1. Connect the one end of the transformer wire and the red R-wire for your heat/cool to the 'R' terminal.
            2. Connect the other end of the transformer to the 'C' terminal.
            3. Connect your other wire (likely white) to the 'W' terminal.
            4. Put the thermostat back on its base.
            4. Plug in the transformer.

            This configuration should keep your thermostat powered. I've had this configuration for 2 months and it works well.
